                    FLD=_name
                    STR=Municipal Supply Intake
                    FLD=_description
                    STR=Intake structure moves up and down to track 65 F isotherm as physical limits permit. Under normal conditions, the TCD is operated between 401 ft. (122.2 m) and 331.5 ft. (101 m); however, under extreme conditions, when the water level is lower, the intake can drop to the elevation of the intake pipe centerline (317 ft.; 96.62 m).
